      <folder name="Processes" id="id-91beefd8cc314eebb4de755ddd2222f0">
        <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Business SWOT Analysis" id="id-88a3393350a149fdab7e2c353b9942d9">
          <documentation>During a Strength, Weakness, Opportunities and Threat (SWOT) analysis it would become clear whether for example a culture is a threat, opportunity or both and needs to be balanced. &#xD;
&#xD;
Threat ID, description&#xD;
A.T.1 Human species are threatened by species of its own sort, due to conflict of interest and survival of the fittest;&#xD;
A.T.2 Human species are threatened by natural weather conditions, like heavy storms/hurricanes; floods; extreme temperatures; &#xD;
A.T.3 Human species are threatened by animals that are higher in the eco-system, or when human species become a threat to this animal and it will defend it self;&#xD;
A.T.4 Human species are threatened by environment conditions, like rocky or dessert areas, earthquakes, sea.&#xD;
Opportunity ID, description&#xD;
A.O.1 Human species will survive longer due to collaboration with each other to withstand threats;&#xD;
A.O.2 Human species will grow stronger due to collaboration for knowledge sharing between generations;&#xD;
A.O.3 Human species can improve quality of life when food and water supplies are preserved for quality and eatable, drinkable quality</documentation>
        </element>
